      <title>Gift of Mana ~~</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=5973#M5973</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;While I understand the thinking behind limiting Gift of Mana's trigger spells, it seems a straight slap in the fact to enchanters that Mez is excluded.&amp;nbsp; I am not a nuker thou I can nuke, so I do no get the benefit that Wizzys, Mages and Necros get from it.&amp;nbsp; Even necro dots are included since they damage.&amp;nbsp; I cannot heal so I do not get the benefit that Shaman, Cleric, and Druids get from it.&amp;nbsp; My most important and largest quantity need for mana is when holding multiple mezzes for long periods of time.&amp;nbsp; It seems that enchanters are the only class completely snuffed by Gift of Mana, and it would be easily solved by including Mez in the triggers.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I am not looking for a bunch of "yah being an enchanter sucks, soe hates up" whine to follow this post.&amp;nbsp; I think being an enchanter rocks and we are quite powerful enough.&amp;nbsp; I am looking for a developer answer to an aa that has very little meaning to only one of the main caster classes, because it excludes the number #1 need for our mana.&amp;nbsp; I understand we are unique in our needs, but we are an integral class in the working of EQ and should not be so obviously ignored.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
